==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ethnical
<hw>Eth"nic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>ethnicus</ets>, Gr. <?/, fr. <?/
nation, <?/ <?/ the nations, heathens, gentiles: cf. F.
<ets>ethnique</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Belonging to races or
nations; based on distinctions of race; ethnological.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pertaining to the gentiles, or nations not converted
to Christianity; heathen; pagan; -- opposed to <contr>Jewish</contr> and
<contr>Christian</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>of or pertaining to a group having a distinct
racial, cultural, religious or linguistic character; <as>as,
<ex>ethnic</ex> differences within a population can cause civil
war</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>being a member of a distinct racial or cultural
minority within a larger population; <as>as, <ex>ethnic</ex> Chinese own
most of the businesses in Indonesia</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ethnic</ent>⟦br⟧
